race.comment: Competitive. WHISKERS HARBOUR (2) looked a run short despite racing favourite at Kalgoorlie first-up and then ran a big relative number beaten a whisker at Northam over this trip. Draws inside today and will be further improved. Just has to hold that level of form to prove hard to beat. SENTIMENTAL LEGEND (14) debuts off a wide gate, but Pike sticks from the solid trials. He strikes at 32% with the top barn and everything points to a bold return. GOD'S GRIN (9) is third up and has been freshened off two near misses. CJP is aboard today for Pike and expect her to feature. BUSY FINGERS (3) resumed with a solid effort at Geraldton and then was heavily bet to win at Northam over 1300m but lacked finishing dash. Loses Pike but draws inside again and is worth another chance. PRETEY ROYAL (7) resumed here with a 1.8L defeat over 1200m. It was a good effort and she's suited over the longer sprint. Has to be kept onside.
